The paper presents a deep learning architecture for point cloud analysis, which involves tasks such as reconstruction, classification, object part segmentation, and shape retrieval. These tasks are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed architecture involves building a Self-Organizing Map (SOM), which is a type of unsupervised learning algorithm, and performing hierarchical feature extraction. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions adjusting the receptive field of the network, which involves conducting point-to-node k nearest neighbor search. This suggests that the paper may be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed architecture has faster training speed due to its parallelizability and simplicity. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
